cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.AR 

This paper is about optimizing matrix multiplication for deep learning, which is a fundamental operation in many deep learning models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the impact of compiler-level optimization on deep learning performance, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) as well.
